      <p>Ever wondered what’s juicing up your favorite WordPress site? In the sprawling jungle of WordPress, with over 60,000 plugins fueling everything from SEO to e-commerce, knowing the tools behind a site’s success is like finding a cheat code. Enter <strong>CRFT Lookup</strong>, your tech-savvy sleuth that uncovers WordPress plugins and more with just a URL and a sly grin.</p>
      <p>Figuring out which plugins power a WordPress site used to require geek-level know-how. Not anymore. CRFT Lookup dives into the code, spots the plugins, and serves up the tech stack of any site—WordPress or otherwise—in a snap.</p>

      <h2>Why Plugin Snooping Matters</h2>
      <p>Before we spill the beans on CRFT Lookup’s detective skills, let’s talk about why plugin detection is a big deal:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Competitor Spy Game</strong>: Want to know how a rival site nails its features? Their plugins reveal the tricks—SEO magic, e-commerce flair, or security muscle.</li>
        <li><strong>Newbie Shortcut</strong>: Just starting with WordPress? See what the pros use and build your site with a head start.</li>
        <li><strong>Expert Edge</strong>: Developers and agencies, this one’s for you. Spot plugin trends and integrations to craft recommendations that make clients go “Wow!”</li>
      </ul>
      <p>CRFT Lookup doesn’t just yell, “It’s Yoast!” It hands you a full tech report—free, fun, and with a sprinkle of swagger.</p>

      <h2>How CRFT Lookup Cracks the Case</h2>
      <p>So, how does CRFT Lookup play plugin detective? Think of it as a digital bloodhound, sniffing through a site’s HTML, JavaScript, asset files, and response headers. With a database of over 2,500 technology fingerprints, it spins up a headless Chromium instance to scan any URL you throw at it. In seconds, it nails down WordPress plugins like WooCommerce, Elementor, or Contact Form 7, plus other tech like frameworks and analytics.</p>
      <p>Drop a WordPress site’s URL into CRFT Lookup, and it’ll hunt for plugins leaving public-facing clues in the code. But it’s not just a WordPress party—this tool can dissect any website, from Basecamp to GitHub, delivering a clean tech stack breakdown that’s easy to digest.</p>

      <h2>Beyond Plugins: The Full Tech Takedown</h2>
      <p>CRFT Lookup isn’t here to half-ass it. It goes all out, giving you a panoramic view of a website’s tech profile. Here’s what you get:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tech Stack Breakdown</strong>: From React and NextJS to Cloudflare and AWS, see the full lineup of frameworks, CMS platforms, and infrastructure.</li>
        <li><strong>Lighthouse Scores</strong>: Google Lighthouse metrics size up performance, accessibility, SEO, and best practices. Is that site zippy or just glitzy? You’ll know.</li>
        <li><strong>Meta Tag Previews</strong>: Peek at how a site looks when shared on Google, Facebook, or Slack. Keep its social game sharp.</li>
        <li><strong>Sitemap Visualization</strong>: Explore a site’s structure with an interactive tree view, mapping pages and navigation like a techy treasure map.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Whether you’re sizing up a WordPress site’s plugins or dissecting a competitor’s tech, these insights help you spot gaps, borrow genius (ethically, duh), and optimize like a boss.</p>

      <h2>Real-World Superpowers</h2>
      <p>What can you <em>do</em> with this tech goldmine? Loads:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Site Owners</strong>: Compare your plugin stack to top dogs and beef up your WordPress setup.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketers</strong>: Spot plugins driving killer campaigns in your niche and steal their thunder.</li>
        <li><strong>Developers</strong>: Uncover plugin patterns and integrations to build slicker solutions.</li>
        <li><strong>Consultants</strong>: Strut into client meetings with tech insights that scream expertise.</li>
      </ul>
