      <h2>Keeping It Ethical (and Free!)</h2>
      <p>Let’s squash any worries: CRFT Lookup only scans publicly accessible data. No creeping into private code or leaking sensitive configs—it’s all on the up-and-up, just reading what’s out there. Think of it as checking a car’s paint job, not popping the hood.</p>
      <p>Oh, and it’s <em>free</em>. Unlimited scans, no wallet required. How do they cash in? By selling primo web design and development services, not by charging for reports. Share your reports via unique URLs, stored for 30 days, and loaded with all the details—great for team huddles or client show-offs.</p>

      <h2>The Fine Print on Plugin Detection</h2>
      <p>To set the record straight: CRFT Lookup doesn’t serve up detailed plugin features, use cases, or performance impacts. It identifies plugins (like Yoast SEO or WooCommerce) and categorizes them based on their technical signatures. For the deep dive, you’ll need to research the plugins yourself—CRFT just points you in the right direction.</p>
      <p>Its detection is tight, thanks to a regularly updated engine that cross-checks multiple clues. But it can only spot plugins with public-facing components—custom or super-stealthy setups might dodge the radar.</p>

      <h2>Ready to Snoop?</h2>
      <p>Whether you’re a WordPress warrior tweaking your site, a developer chasing tech inspo, or just a curious web geek, CRFT Lookup is your go-to for uncovering the tech behind any site. Fire up a scan, share the results, and build smarter. You might just find the secret sauce that takes your site from “fine” to “fire.”</p>
